I did a little more investigating. I believe now the null pointer is coming
strchr inside fastforward_buf_to_lnum. when the completion is initially added
after typing "Oif<C-Space>", the content of the file passed to
get_linematch_results contains the string terminator '\0'

the fastforward_buf_to_lnum will use strchr repeatedly find '\n' to get to the
line number of the diff hunk, and when it sees a '\0', it will return NULL


```
static void get_linematch_results(lua_State *lstate, mmfile_t *ma, mmfile_t *mb, int start_a,
                                  int count_a, int start_b, int count_b, bool iwhite)
{
  // get the pointer to char of the start of the diff to pass it to linematch algorithm
  const char *diff_begin[2] = { ma->ptr, mb->ptr };
  int diff_length[2] = { count_a, count_b };

  fastforward_buf_to_lnum(&diff_begin[0], (linenr_T)start_a + 1);
  fastforward_buf_to_lnum(&diff_begin[1], (linenr_T)start_b + 1);

  int *decisions = NULL;
  size_t decisions_length = linematch_nbuffers(diff_begin, diff_length, 2, &decisions, iwhite);
  ...
```

```
void fastforward_buf_to_lnum(const char **s, linenr_T lnum)
{
  for (int i = 0; i < lnum - 1; i++) {
    *s = strchr(*s, '\n');
    if (!*s) {
      return;
    }
    (*s)++;
  }
}
```
```
static size_t line_len(const char *s)
{
  char *end = strchr(s, '\n');
  if (end) {
    return (size_t)(end - s);
  }
  return strlen(s);
}
```

so one solution would be to preprocess the input to remove the string terminating character '\0' from the input. 

Or else fastforward_buf_to_lnum (and linematch.c:line_len) would need to be modified to accomodate '\0' characters in the algorithm. They need to have a 'strchr' that continues the search past '\0' characterss
